title: American Jet Shoots Down Turkish Drone in Syria
description: The Pentagon said the drone had been observed carrying out airstrikes shortly before flying within about 550 yards of U.S. forces.

title: Friday Briefing: Strike Kills 51 in Ukrainian Village
description: Plus the Nobel in literature.

title: Explosion in Ukraine Kills at Least 51 Gathered for a Wake
description: Ukrainians officials said a Russian strike had killed at least 51 people in a tiny village with no obvious military or industrial targets nearby.

title: Mexico-U.S. Ties: What to Know About Migration, Fentanyl and Guns
description: Tensions over soaring migration, overdose deaths and the role of U.S. guns in cartel violence have strained relations.

title: Putin Suggests New Narrative for Prigozhin Plane Crash: Cocaine and Grenades
description: The Russian president said grenade fragments were found in the bodies recovered from the crash site after the Wagner mercenary leader’s plane went down in August.

title: Floorboards (Possibly) Trodden by Shakespeare Are Found in England
description: Boards dating to the 15th century were found during renovations at St. George’s Guildhall. However, some Shakespeare experts are not certain the playwright touched them.

title: France Begins a Vaccination Program for 64 Million Ducks
description: The inoculations are aimed at curbing the spread of a lethal strain of bird flu, and to support foie gras, a cherished delicacy.

title: Jaswant Singh Chail Is Sentenced in Windsor Castle Crossbow Case
description: Jaswant Singh Chail, 21, was convicted of treason. His intrusion on the grounds of Windsor Castle on Christmas morning 2021 was foiled by the police.

title: Protests to Egypt’s Presidential Elections Grow as Sisi Announces Campaign
description: Voters will chose a leader in December. It will likely be President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi, though with the economy in dire straits, protests are gaining momentum.

title: Putin Claims Russia Successfully Tested a Nuclear-Powered Missile
description: “No one in their sound mind will use a nuclear weapon against Russia,” the Russian president said. The test could not be independently verified.

title: Visa Applicants’ Social Media Data Doesn’t Help Screen for Terrorism, Documents Show
description: A Trump-era practice of vetting the social media profiles of visitors has provided scant value, intelligence officials concluded. But the Biden administration has kept the policy in place.

title: Bobi Wine Says Ugandan Police Put Him Under House Arrest
description: The police denied that they had arrested Bobi Wine, a challenger to Uganda’s autocratic president, saying they “escorted” him from an airport to his home.

title: TikTok Shuts Shop Feature in Indonesia Following Ban
description: TikTok’s retail ambitions have confronted an obstacle in its second-largest market, which views the app as a threat to local businesses.

title: Nobel Prize in Literature: 2023 Laureate to Be Announced Today
description: The accolade, which is awarded for a writer’s entire body of work, is the world’s most prestigious literature prize.

title: Russia-Ukraine War : Biden Worries U.S. Political Tumult Could Disrupt Aid to Ukraine
description: The president emphasized bipartisan support for the assistance, as a power struggle in the Republican Party has left the House of Representatives without a leader and brought legislative business to a halt.

title: Blinken, Garland and Mayorkas Land in Mexico to Tackle Range of Issues
description: The secretary of state, Attorney General Merrick B. Garland and Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas plan to meet with Mexico’s leader and other officials to cement strategy.

title: US Sends Ukraine 1.1 Million Rounds of Ammunition Seized from Iran
description: The military transferred rounds for machine guns that it said had been bound for Yemen.

title: With Iranian Girl in Coma, Suspicion Falls on Government
description: Exactly what happened to Armita Geravand, 16, is unclear, but the circumstances have fueled accusations that agents enforcing Iran’s dress code must have harmed her.

title: Thursday Briefing
description: The fallout from the ouster of the House speaker.

title: A Wartime Election in Ukraine? It’s a Political Hot Potato.
description: In normal circumstances, President Volodymyr Zelensky would be running for re-election next spring. Analysts say an election is unlikely, but the prospect is causing some anxiety in Kyiv.
